---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Privacy | NextMetro"
  description="Privacy information for NextMetro, the iPhone and Apple Watch app for timing your Metro ride."
>
  <section class="section tight content-page">
    <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
    <h1>NextMetro Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      NextMetro is designed to help you time your trip without creating an
      account, tracking you, or building a commute profile.
    </p>

    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Data We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        NextMetro does not collect personal data from you and does not require
        an account. Your WMATA API key, walk buffer, commute window, and route
        settings are stored on your devices so the app can request relevant train
        predictions.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Location and Tracking</h2>
      <p>
        NextMetro does not request location access and does not track you across
        apps or websites.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Apple Watch Sync</h2>
      <p>
        If you use the Apple Watch app, NextMetro syncs your WMATA API key and
        commute settings from your iPhone to your Apple Watch using Apple's
        WatchConnectivity framework.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>WMATA</h2>
      <p>
        NextMetro sends your WMATA API key to WMATA only when requesting train
        predictions. WMATA provides the arrival data and may process requests
        according to its own terms and policies.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Notifications</h2>
      <p>
        If you enable notifications, NextMetro schedules local reminders on your
        device so you know when to start walking. Notification permissions can be
        changed in iOS or watchOS Settings.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about privacy can be sent to
        <a href="mailto:support@nextmetro.app">support@nextmetro.app</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
